      • add

        public int add​(int i,
               NodeList nodes)
        This moves the node at position i forwards one, and replaces it with 
        nodes
        Returns:
        The new index of the last node added. Not the index of the node after it, or before it, but it. So if a list of length=3 is added, the return value should be i+3-1.

      • replace

        public int replace​(int i,
                   NodeList nodes)
        This calls remove(i), then add(i, nodes); The result returned is the result of the latter function.
        So x.replace(3, y) removes the item at position 3 of x, and inserts each node of y into x starting at position 3. If x had a size() of 2, the result returned will be 4, which is the position of the last node inserted into y.
